<br>
I want to see a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>wizard-only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> charm/item with an effect that either increases your chance to crit, or gives a chance of a double-crit.  Hmm...maybe it could even just double the &quot;focus&quot; damage like crits originally did.<br>
<br>
Currently, with a 20% damage focus, Agnarr's Thunder can do this:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Innate crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 1.5 + 2305 * 0.2 = 3918<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCF3 crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 2 + 2305 * 0.2 = 5071<br>
<br>
<br>
With the suggested <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>wizard-only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> item (doubling focus damage), you could do this:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Innate crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 1.5 + 2305 * 0.2 * 2 = 4379<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCF3 crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 2 + 2305 * 0.2 * 2 = 5532<br>
<br>
<br>
With the suggested <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>wizard-only</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> item (giving double-crits), you could do this:<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Innate crit + Innate crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 1.5 + 2305 * 0.5 + 2305 * 0.2 = 5071<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>SCF3 crit + Innate crit:</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2305 * 2 + 2305 * 0.5 + 2305 * 0.2 = 6223<br>
<br>
<br>
Basically, the maximum increase in damage this item would give over current situation is 1152 with AT.  The idea is that whenever you get a SCF3 crit, or an innate crit, the item gives you a random roll attempt for another innate crit from 0% to 50% extra damage.<br>
<br>
Why?  Well, because all classes get access to SCF3 and Fury of Magic/Fury of Magic Mastery.<br>
<br>
Does anyone actually know what the difference is between Fury of Magic and Fury of Magic Mastery???  From what I can tell, FoMM gives 2% chance per rank.  Does FoM give the same 2%?  If so, then why the different name?<br>
<br>
The only difference in crit ability between wizards and non-wizards appears to be the 7% we get from SCFM in our class skills. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59003"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.nc.rr.com/jelong/users/web/Cedrich/rofl.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
